cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.PL, cs.SE 

This paper discusses privacy concerns related to third-party tracking on the web and proposes a privacy-preserving web architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper discusses the tracking of users across different websites, cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with privacy concerns, cs.PL (Programming Languages) as the paper proposes a new web architecture, and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it discusses the implementation of the proposed architecture.
